.SH NAME
Net::Nostr::FileMetadata \- NIP\-94 File Metadata events
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&    use Net::Nostr::FileMetadata;
\&
\&    # Build a kind 1063 file metadata event
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::FileMetadata\->to_event(
\&        pubkey   => $pubkey,
\&        content  => \*(AqA scenic photo\*(Aq,
\&        url      => \*(Aqhttps://example.com/photo.jpg\*(Aq,
\&        m        => \*(Aqimage/jpeg\*(Aq,
\&        x        => $sha256_hex,
\&        ox       => $original_sha256_hex,
\&        dim      => \*(Aq1920x1080\*(Aq,
\&        alt      => \*(AqA scenic photo\*(Aq,
\&        blurhash => \*(AqeVF$^OI\*(Aq,
\&        fallback => [\*(Aqhttps://alt.example.com/photo.jpg\*(Aq],
\&    );
\&
\&    # Parse file metadata from a kind 1063 event
\&    my $fm = Net::Nostr::FileMetadata\->from_event($event);
\&    say $fm\->url;       # https://example.com/photo.jpg
\&    say $fm\->m;         # image/jpeg
\&    say $fm\->dim;       # 1920x1080
\&    say $fm\->alt;       # A scenic photo
\&
\&    # Validate a file metadata event
\&    Net::Nostr::FileMetadata\->validate($event);
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Implements NIP\-94 (File Metadata). Provides methods to build kind 1063
file metadata events, parse them, and validate their structure.
.PP
Kind 1063 events describe shared files with metadata tags. The \f(CW\*(C`content\*(C'\fR
field holds a description or caption. Required tags are \f(CW\*(C`url\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`m\*(C'\fR
(MIME type), \f(CW\*(C`x\*(C'\fR (SHA\-256 hash of the file), and \f(CW\*(C`ox\*(C'\fR (SHA\-256 hash of
the original file before any server transformations).
.PP
Optional tags include \f(CW\*(C`size\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`dim\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`magnet\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`i\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`blurhash\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`thumb\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`image\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`summary\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`alt\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`fallback\*(C'\fR (zero or more), and
\&\f(CW\*(C`service\*(C'\fR.
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
.IX Header "CONSTRUCTOR"
.SS new
.IX Subsection "new"
.Vb 6
\&    my $fm = Net::Nostr::FileMetadata\->new(
\&        url  => \*(Aqhttps://example.com/photo.jpg\*(Aq,
\&        m    => \*(Aqimage/jpeg\*(Aq,
\&        x    => $sha256_hex,
\&        ox   => $original_sha256_hex,
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a new \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::FileMetadata\*(C'\fR object. All fields are optional.
\&\f(CW\*(C`fallback\*(C'\fR defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR. Croaks on unknown arguments. Typically
returned by "from_event"; calling \f(CW\*(C`new\*(C'\fR directly is useful for testing.
.SH "CLASS METHODS"
.IX Header "CLASS METHODS"
.SS to_event
.IX Subsection "to_event"
.Vb 10
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::FileMetadata\->to_event(
\&        pubkey     => $hex_pubkey,
\&        content    => \*(AqA scenic photo\*(Aq,
\&        url        => \*(Aqhttps://example.com/photo.jpg\*(Aq,
\&        m          => \*(Aqimage/jpeg\*(Aq,
\&        x          => $sha256_hex,
\&        ox         => $original_sha256_hex,
\&        size       => \*(Aq1048576\*(Aq,
\&        dim        => \*(Aq1920x1080\*(Aq,
\&        magnet     => \*(Aqmagnet:?xt=urn:btih:abc\*(Aq,
\&        i          => \*(Aqinfohash\*(Aq,
\&        blurhash   => \*(AqeVF$^OI\*(Aq,
\&        thumb      => \*(Aqhttps://example.com/thumb.jpg\*(Aq,
\&        thumb_hash => $thumb_sha256_hex,
\&        image      => \*(Aqhttps://example.com/preview.jpg\*(Aq,
\&        image_hash => $preview_sha256_hex,
\&        summary    => \*(Aqexcerpt text\*(Aq,
\&        alt        => \*(Aqaccessibility description\*(Aq,
\&        fallback   => [\*(Aqhttps://alt.example.com/photo.jpg\*(Aq],
\&        service    => \*(Aqnip96\*(Aq,
\&        extra_tags => [[\*(Aqt\*(Aq, \*(Aqphoto\*(Aq]],
\&        created_at => time(),
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 1063 Net::Nostr::Event. \f(CW\*(C`url\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`m\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`x\*(C'\fR, and \f(CW\*(C`ox\*(C'\fR are
required. \f(CW\*(C`x\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`ox\*(C'\fR must be 64\-character lowercase hex (SHA\-256). \f(CW\*(C`m\*(C'\fR
must be a lowercase MIME type containing a slash. \f(CW\*(C`dim\*(C'\fR, if provided, must be
in \f(CW\*(C`<width>x<height>\*(C'\fR format.
.PP
\&\f(CW\*(C`thumb\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`image\*(C'\fR accept an optional hash via \f(CW\*(C`thumb_hash\*(C'\fR and
\&\f(CW\*(C`image_hash\*(C'\fR. \f(CW\*(C`fallback\*(C'\fR accepts an arrayref of URLs. \f(CW\*(C`extra_tags\*(C'\fR allows
injecting additional tags.
.PP
Any remaining arguments (\f(CW\*(C`pubkey\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`content\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`created_at\*(C'\fR) are passed
through to "new" in Net::Nostr::Event.
.SS from_event
.IX Subsection "from_event"
.Vb 1
\&    my $fm = Net::Nostr::FileMetadata\->from_event($event);
.Ve
.PP
Parses a kind 1063 event into a \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::FileMetadata\*(C'\fR object. Returns
\&\f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR if the event is not kind 1063.
.PP
.Vb 4
\&    my $fm = Net::Nostr::FileMetadata\->from_event($event);
\&    say $fm\->url;
\&    say $fm\->m;
\&    say $fm\->size;
.Ve
.SS validate
.IX Subsection "validate"
.Vb 1
\&    Net::Nostr::FileMetadata\->validate($event);
.Ve
.PP
Validates that an event is a well\-formed NIP\-94 file metadata event. Croaks
if the kind is not 1063 or if any required tag (\f(CW\*(C`url\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`m\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`x\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`ox\*(C'\fR)
is missing. Returns 1 on success.
.PP
.Vb 2
\&    eval { Net::Nostr::FileMetadata\->validate($event) };
\&    warn "Invalid: $@" if $@;
.Ve
.SH ACCESSORS
.IX Header "ACCESSORS"
.SS url
.IX Subsection "url"
File URL.
.SS m
.IX Subsection "m"
MIME type (e.g. \f(CW\*(Aqimage/jpeg\*(Aq\fR). Must be lowercase.
.SS x
.IX Subsection "x"
SHA\-256 hex hash of the file.
.SS ox
.IX Subsection "ox"
SHA\-256 hex hash of the original file before server transformations.
.SS size
.IX Subsection "size"
File size in bytes (string).
.SS dim
.IX Subsection "dim"
Dimensions in \f(CW\*(C`<width>x<height>\*(C'\fR format (e.g. \f(CW\*(Aq1920x1080\*(Aq\fR).
.SS magnet
.IX Subsection "magnet"
Magnet URI.
.SS i
.IX Subsection "i"
Torrent infohash.
.SS blurhash
.IX Subsection "blurhash"
Blurhash string for loading placeholder.
.SS thumb
.IX Subsection "thumb"
Thumbnail URL (same aspect ratio as original).
.SS thumb_hash
.IX Subsection "thumb_hash"
SHA\-256 hex hash of the thumbnail.
.SS image
.IX Subsection "image"
Preview image URL (same dimensions as original).
.SS image_hash
.IX Subsection "image_hash"
SHA\-256 hex hash of the preview image.
.SS summary
.IX Subsection "summary"
Text excerpt.
.SS alt
.IX Subsection "alt"
Accessibility description.
.SS fallback
.IX Subsection "fallback"
Arrayref of fallback file source URLs.
.SS service
.IX Subsection "service"
Service type serving the file (e.g. NIP\-96).
